Orchestrator
(Data Factory)
• Connections
• Data Sets
• Pipelines
• Triggers
Processor
(Spark)
• Libraries
• Scripts
• Jobs
Store
(ADLS)
• Structure
• Governance
Presentation
(SQL DW)
• Loading
Artifact
Immutable
Includes everything needed to deploy
Build
Pipeline
Always CREATES an artifact
Sometimes compiles code, sometimes copies things
Release
Pipeline
Always DEPLOYS an artifact
To an environment
Environment
A target system where the artifact is deployed
i.e. Production data factory
Unit Test
• Generally in Build pipeline
• Tests specific thing
• i.e. function in Python library
• Input vs output
• Known bad data input
• Known good data input
• Do lookups work as expected?
Integration Test
• Generally in Release pipeline
• Tests wider systems
• i.e. ADF pipeline using Python library in Spark
• Input vs output
• Generated data set designed around testing
• Boundary conditions (i.e. times in am/pm 24h vs 12h)
• Are files where expected?
• Is all expected data present
Development
• Development takes place
here
• Usually product specific
• May be a laptop
• May be a web service
• Who – Data engineers,
developers
• Data - Generally a
generated but
representative data set
(i.e. the right schema but
not real data)
Test
• Designed for tests
• Usually process specific
“end to end”
• No human interaction
where possible
• Automated tests
• Who – Nobody, results
report back to Azure
DevOps for approval
• Data – Generally a
dataset architected
around tests. Not
necessarily same schema,
definitely not real data, as
small as possible to carry
out testing
(Pre-Production)
• Usually not needed
• Just confirms no
deployment issues
• Who – Early access users
• Data –This will use the
production lake
Production
• End user environment
• No human admin ideally
• Who – Everyone
including analysts EXCEPT
data scientists
• Data – Production lake
Experimental
• For Data science
• Not development
• Experimentation
• Less governance
• Separated for performance reasons
• Who – Data scientists
• Data – Generally copied to another lake as needed
• Removed as soon as possible
